---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BoxingDayCountdown from '../components/BoxingDayCountdown.jsx';

const leftEmojis = [
	{ emoji: '🎁', size: 48, rotation: -15, top: '10%', side: '2%', delay: 0 },
	{ emoji: '🛍️', size: 32, rotation: 12, top: '25%', side: '8%', delay: 0.5 },
	{ emoji: '🦌', size: 40, rotation: -8, top: '45%', side: '4%', delay: 1 },
	{ emoji: '❄️', size: 28, rotation: 15, top: '65%', side: '10%', delay: 1.5 },
	{ emoji: '🎁', size: 44, rotation: -12, top: '80%', side: '6%', delay: 2 },
	{ emoji: '🛍️', size: 36, rotation: 8, top: '35%', side: '2%', delay: 2.5 },
];

const rightEmojis = [
	{ emoji: '🦌', size: 36, rotation: -5, top: '15%', side: '3%', delay: 3 },
	{ emoji: '❄️', size: 48, rotation: 14, top: '30%', side: '9%', delay: 3.5 },
	{ emoji: '🎁', size: 30, rotation: -10, top: '50%', side: '5%', delay: 4 },
	{ emoji: '🛍️', size: 42, rotation: 6, top: '70%', side: '8%', delay: 4.5 },
	{ emoji: '🦌', size: 28, rotation: -15, top: '85%', side: '4%', delay: 5 },
	{ emoji: '❄️', size: 46, rotation: 10, top: '40%', side: '2%', delay: 5.5 },
];
---

<Layout
	title="Boxing Day Countdown — Days Until Boxing Day | Clockr"
	description="How many days until Boxing Day? Live countdown to 26 December — showing days, hours, minutes and seconds until the next Boxing Day."
	category="holidays"
>
	<div class="bxd-page">
		<section class="bxd-hero" aria-label="Boxing Day countdown">
			<div class="bxd-hero-decor" aria-hidden="true">
				{
					leftEmojis.map(({ emoji, size, rotation, top, side, delay }) => (
						<span
							class="bxd-float-emoji bxd-float-emoji--left"
							style={`font-size:${size}px;top:${top};left:${side};--rotation:${rotation}deg;animation-delay:${delay}s`}
						>
							{emoji}
						</span>
					))
				}
				{
					rightEmojis.map(({ emoji, size, rotation, top, side, delay }) => (
						<span
							class="bxd-float-emoji bxd-float-emoji--right"
							style={`font-size:${size}px;top:${top};right:${side};--rotation:${rotation}deg;animation-delay:${delay}s`}
						>
							{emoji}
						</span>
					))
				}
			</div>

			<div class="bxd-hero-centre">
				<div class="bxd-eyebrow">
					<span class="bxd-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
					HOLIDAY COUNTDOWNS
				</div>
				<h1 class="bxd-hero-title">Boxing Day Countdown</h1>
				<p class="bxd-subtitle">Counting down to Boxing Day</p>

				<BoxingDayCountdown client:load />
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="bxd-body">
			<section class="bxd-how">
				<h2 class="bxd-section-title">How it works</h2>
				<div class="bxd-how-card">
					<p>
						Boxing Day takes its name from a long-standing British tradition in
						which employers gave servants, tradespeople, and the less fortunate
						a "Christmas box" — a gift or gratuity — on the day after Christmas.
						The practice dates back to at least the Victorian era and draws on
						even older customs of charitable giving during the twelve days of
						Christmas. For household staff who worked on Christmas Day itself,
						26 December was their day off and their chance to receive thanks in
						the form of food, money, or goods.
					</p>
					<p>
						Today, Boxing Day is a major public holiday across the United
						Kingdom and much of the Commonwealth — including Canada, Australia,
						New Zealand, and South Africa. Banks, schools, and many workplaces
						close for the day. It has also become one of the biggest retail
						events of the year, with post-Christmas sales drawing crowds to shops
						and online stores. Sporting traditions are equally strong: football
						fixtures fill stadiums in England, while horse racing meetings such
						as the King George VI Chase at Kempton Park are fixtures of the
						seasonal calendar.
					</p>
					<p>
						Despite sharing Christmas itself, Boxing Day is not widely
						recognised or observed in the United States. Americans typically
						return to work on 26 December unless it falls on a weekend, and the
						name carries little cultural weight there. The countdown on this
						page targets midnight on 26 December of the current year — and if
						that date has already passed, it automatically rolls forward to 26
						December of the following year.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="bxd-faq">
				<h2 class="bxd-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
				<div class="bxd-faq-list">
					<details class="bxd-faq-item">
						<summary class="bxd-faq-question">When is Boxing Day?</summary>
						<div class="bxd-faq-answer">
							<p>
								Boxing Day is always on 26 December — the day immediately after
								Christmas Day. It does not move from year to year. The live
								countdown at the top of this page shows the exact date and time
								remaining until the next 26 December.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bxd-faq-item">
						<summary class="bxd-faq-question">Why is it called Boxing Day?</summary>
						<div class="bxd-faq-answer">
							<p>
								The name comes from the tradition of giving "Christmas boxes" to
								servants, tradespeople, and those in need on the day after
								Christmas. Employers and wealthy households would present boxes
								containing gifts, bonuses, or leftover food as a token of
								gratitude. The custom was well established in Victorian Britain
								and reflects centuries of post-Christmas charitable giving.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bxd-faq-item">
						<summary class="bxd-faq-question">Is Boxing Day a public holiday?</summary>
						<div class="bxd-faq-answer">
							<p>
								Yes, in the United Kingdom and many Commonwealth countries
								including Canada, Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa.
								Banks, government offices, schools, and many businesses close
								for the day. When 26 December falls on a weekend, some countries
								observe a substitute public holiday on the following Monday.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bxd-faq-item">
						<summary class="bxd-faq-question">Which countries celebrate Boxing Day?</summary>
						<div class="bxd-faq-answer">
							<p>
								Boxing Day is primarily observed in the United Kingdom, Ireland,
								and Commonwealth nations such as Canada, Australia, New Zealand,
								and South Africa. It is also recognised in some other countries
								with British colonial ties. It is not a public holiday in the
								United States, most of continental Europe, or much of Asia.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bxd-faq-item">
						<summary class="bxd-faq-question">Is Boxing Day celebrated in the US?</summary>
						<div class="bxd-faq-answer">
							<p>
								No. Boxing Day is not a recognised holiday in the United States.
								While Americans celebrate Christmas on 25 December, 26 December is
								typically a normal working day unless it falls on a weekend. The
								post-Christmas sales tradition exists in the US but is not tied
								to the Boxing Day name or public holiday status.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bxd-faq-item">
						<summary class="bxd-faq-question">What traditions are associated with Boxing Day?</summary>
						<div class="bxd-faq-answer">
							<p>
								Common Boxing Day traditions include post-Christmas sales
								shopping, watching or attending football matches and horse
								racing, family gatherings and leftover Christmas feasts, and
								charitable giving. In some communities, Boxing Day hunts and
								outdoor walks remain popular ways to shake off the Christmas
								indulgence and enjoy time with friends and family.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>
			</section>

			<div class="bxd-related">
				<h3 class="bxd-related-title">Related tools</h3>
				<div class="bxd-related-grid">
					<a href="/days-until-christmas" class="bxd-related-card"
						><span class="bxd-related-name">Days Until Christmas</span></a
					>
					<a href="/days-until-new-year" class="bxd-related-card"
						><span class="bxd-related-name">Days Until New Year</span></a
					>
					<a href="/days-until-black-friday" class="bxd-related-card"
						><span class="bxd-related-name">Black Friday Countdown</span></a
					>
					<a href="/days-until-valentines" class="bxd-related-card"
						><span class="bxd-related-name">Days Until Valentine's Day</span></a
					>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.bxd-page {
		width: 100%;
	}

	.bxd-hero {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100%;
		padding: 72px 24px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a0a0b, #18181b);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.35);
		overflow: hidden;
		position: relative;
		min-height: 320px;
	}

	.bxd-hero-decor {
		position: absolute;
		inset: 0;
		pointer-events: none;
		user-select: none;
	}

	.bxd-float-emoji {
		position: absolute;
		display: inline-block;
		line-height: 1;
		transform: rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		animation: bxd-float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.bxd-float-emoji {
			opacity: 0.35;
		}
	}

	@keyframes bxd-float {
		0%,
		100% {
			transform: translateY(0) rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		}
		33% {
			transform: translateY(-10px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) - 3deg));
		}
		66% {
			transform: translateY(-5px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) + 3deg));
		}
	}

	.bxd-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
	}

	.bxd-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.bxd-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #16a34a);
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.45);
	}

	.bxd-hero-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 64px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #16a34a);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.bxd-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0 0 28px;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown-widget) {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown) {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-end;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px 12px;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown-block) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown-num) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #16a34a);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		min-width: 64px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown-num--days) {
		font-size: clamp(80px, 13vw, 120px);
		letter-spacing: -4px;
		min-width: 100px;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown-sep) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 26px;
		padding: 0 2px;
	}

	:global(.bxd-countdown-unit) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
	}

	:global(.bxd-target-date) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(15px, 2.5vw, 18px);
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		margin: 24px 0 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.bxd-body {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 48px 24px 60px;
	}

	.bxd-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.bxd-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.bxd-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.2);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.bxd-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.bxd-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.bxd-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.bxd-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.bxd-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.2);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.bxd-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #16a34a);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.bxd-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.bxd-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #16a34a);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.bxd-faq-item[open] .bxd-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.bxd-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.bxd-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.bxd-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.bxd-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.bxd-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.bxd-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.bxd-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.45);
	}

	.bxd-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #16a34a);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.bxd-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
